Hi,<br><br><div><span class="gmail_quote">On 8/25/06, <b class="gmail_sendername">Sven Stork</b> &lt;<a href="mailto:stork@hlrs.de">stork@hlrs.de</a>&gt; wrote:</span><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="border-left: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 0.8ex; padding-left: 1ex;">
Hello Miguel,<br><br>this is caused by the shared memory mempool. Per default this shared memory<br>mapping has a size of 512 MB. You can use the &quot;mpool_sm_size&quot; parameter to<br>reduce size e.g.<br><br>mpirun -mca mpool_sm_size &lt;SIZE&gt; ...
</blockquote><div><br><br>using <br>mpirun -mca mpool_sm_size 0 <br>is acceptable ?<br>to what will it fallback ? sockets? pipes? tcp? smoke signals?<br><br>thankyou very much by the fast answer.<br> </div><br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="border-left: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 0.8ex; padding-left: 1ex;">
